If f is first-order continuously differentiable, then f is convex iff
f(\boldsymbol {y}) \geq  f(\boldsymbol {x}) + \langle  \nabla  f(\boldsymbol {x}), \boldsymbol {y} - \boldsymbol {x}
\rangle

