    Recall that

    \begin {align*}
      P_{e}(g) &= \sum _{x}\sum _y P_{XY}(x, y) \cdot  \mathbf {1}_{x \neq  g(y)} \\
      &= \sum _{y} P_Y(y) \sum _{x} P_{X|Y}(x|y) \mathbf {1}_{x \neq  g(y)} \\
      &= \sum _{y} P_Y(y) (1 - P_{X|Y}(g(y)|y)) \\
    \end {align*}

To minimize this, we take

  \begin {align*}
    g^*(y) = \arg \max _{x} P_{X|Y}(x | y)
  \end {align*}

as desired.

